node.text:
Ad| Jumping rope has become a favorite way to move because it's convenient and quick! You can get a great workout in 5 - 20 minutes. This is something you can do from anywhere.

When I jump, I need activewear that stays in place and the @underarmourwomen Rush No-Slip leggings and Infinity Bra definitely fits the bill. These do not go ANYWHERE, and offer support and breathability for your sweatiest workout.

Try this Beginner's Jump Rope workout and let me know how you like it! #UAFitClass

node.text:
Preparing your muscles for a workout is an important step that we all tend to forget sometimes. Warming up with activation exercises is works to not only get the most out of your workout, but also make sure your muscles are ready to safely move through each workout.

This leg day warm up is super easy and quick, and can even be used as a quick workout if you perform them in 3 sets of 25 - 20.

For leg day, I always wear leggings that allow me to get a full range of motion and The @underarmourwomen In-Bloom Collection is perfect, because it is soft and supportive and moves with your body! With the stay in place band the Meridian leggings are squat approved 👌🏾

Remember: always move through your exercises with intention and focus! 

#uainbloom

node.text:
Sponsored | I CANNOT express how joyful I am about the Spring weather FINALLY being here! I love mixing up my workouts with a few outdoor activities when it's warm outside.

Here is a quick, one band strength workout you can do anywhere. The great thing about it is you can choose the length of the workout by performing anywhere between 2 and 5 sets!

This workout will get you pretty sweaty, so wearing @underarmourwomen Iso-Chill activewear will help keep you cool.  I could FEEL the fabric working to cool me down throughout my workout AND it helped me go longer and harder.

So go ahead – grab a band, head to your favorite park and have fun with this simple workout!

node.title: The Do Anywhere Single-Band Strength Workout

Self Awareness

Self Love

node.text:
I believe that movement should be joyful and fun and this workout definitely delivers! #supernaturalpartner

@GetSupernatural is a virtual reality workout on the Oculus Quest 2. It's packed with hundreds of workouts that lets you travel to settings around the world. You can customize based on intensity and music genre.

When I'm working out, I like to believe I'm taking down hostile targets and saving the world – I've always wanted to experience being a superhero and I think this is the closest I'll get 💪🏾.

#GetSupernatural today, get moving and fall in love with exercise!

#iamSupernatural #SupernaturalPartner

node.text:
I cut my hair and I LOVE it 

But I didn't do it because I wanted to or wanted it short.

I did it because I wasn't taking care of it properly which led to breakage, dryness and horrible ends. 

I NEEDED to cut it.

Even though I want my hair long, those dead ends were ultimately a hindrance.

Guess what? This happens in your life too.

You might find something in your life that you don't WANT gone, but it will ultimately hinder you from your goals – relationships, habits, and yes, even dieting and overexercise...

I want to encourage you to cut that shit off today, and if you're comfortable, tell me what you need to cut off in the comments 👇🏾

Love ya'll! #liveinthemoment #liveyourbestlife

node.text:
Today, I find myself immensely grateful. 

Last year my credit score was like 530, I was in a precarious living situation, I found myself very depressed and did not know how I was going to move foward.

I decided to work through it – I was used to blocking mt emotions but I let them in and worked through them, and that allowed me to get clear on what I wantee. I set goals for my life and startED SPRINTING towards them.

I grew my Instagram account teaching something I am passionate about.

Got to partner with brands I believe in.

I paid off almost 15k in unsecured consumer debt.

Raised my credit score about 120 points.

Qualified for a home. 

Now I'm a homeowner.

And today, all of it hit me.

I could call myself "lucky" but it wasn't luck. I decided to be relentless and go after this. 

That relentless pursuit and by the Grace of God, I got here today. 

And I am so grateful. 

My next goals is to help secure the bag for those that I love.

node.text:
#Ad| Period self-care is an absolute must, especially if you experience painful cramping. Grab your favorite chocolate and get ready for some much-needed self-care tips!

@thisisL has everything you need for that time of the month (and the whole month) Ya'll are already making regular @Target trips, so go ahead and add these to your essentials list!

1. Move your body.

When I'm cramping, the first thing I think to do is just lay there with a blanket over my head, but I find that light movement really helps. Try a yoga flow or a walk.

I can move comfortably in the L. Tampons AND they are made with organic cotton (without the organic price tag!) 

2. Use heat

My absolute favorite thing is to take a hot shower or bath. You can take time to really pamper yourself and the L. Period Care wash is the PERFECT product to use during your period and L.’s Daily Care wash for the rest of the month. Make sure you are only using the wash externally!

Get the shower going and you can feel the pain and stress melting away!
 
3. Stay hydrated

Keeping hydrated helps to reduce bloating during your period! This is something you can do all the time so you're feeling your best before your period starts.

You can also try drinking hot water or herbal tea during your period to increase blood flow and help relax your muscles. Good hydration also keeps things moving, so I love to have L. Wipes in my purse. They are fragrance-free and gentle on your skin.

What's YOUR favorite period self care tip? Comment below!

When I jump, I need activewear that stays in place and the @underarmourwomen Rush No-Slip leggings and Infinity Bra definitely fits the bill. These do not go ANYWHERE, and offer support and breathability for your sweatiest workout.

Try this Beginner's Jump Rope workout and let me know how you like it! #UAFitClass

node.text:
Ad| When I started exercising in college, my only goal was to get as skinny as I could. 

Now I understand that exercise helps you live. It helps you be energized for those special moments with friends and family.

When I work out, I want to wear gear that I look and feel supported in, and the @underarmourwomen Rush No-Slip waistband stays where I need it to. I can focus on my performance instead of adjusting my leggings.

Move your body – not to alter your appearance but to be stronger.

Faster.

More free.

Exercise to live, don't live to exercise. #UAFitClass

node.text:
I thought getting super thin would make me happy.

The pursuit of thinness only left me more empty, and in an endless cycle of trying to obtain a perfect image. 

I lost the weight and still thought I wasn't attractive and kept seeking to change something – better abs, better butt. It was painful dieting and forcing myself to do exercise as a punishment.

When you pursue health and fitness with a mindset of changing yourself to look better, you set yourself for more heartache. 

The pursuit of a "snatched body" will never be enough to fix poor body image.

Bodies change and your happiness cannot be contingent on something so malleable.

You need to focus on your mindset first, learn to appreciate your value and your unique gift to this world.

Set from @cuup

#bodyimage #bodyconfidence #bodyacceptance #positivebodyimage
